modules.description: Provides functions to parse and apply runtime configuration options from the command line, including backtrace activation, hash table seed settings, and garbage collector parameters. Operates on command-line arguments and environment variables to modify OCaml runtime behavior. Used to fine-tune application performance and debugging features without changing code.

Provides command-line options to configure the OCaml runtime, including backtrace handling, hash table randomization, and garbage collector settings. Operates on boolean flags, Gc.control records, and command-line terms. Enables fine-grained control over runtime behavior through explicit configuration parameters.
